<section class="markdown" data-translation="true">
## Passing Arguments

Currently `view.phtml` is output from `app:/test/index.php` as follows:

```php
OP()->Template('view.phtml');
```

To pass arguments, modify it as follows:

```php
//  Create an argument.
$args = [
    'p' => 'The NEW WORLD is a new world.',
];

//  Pass it as the second argument.
OP()->Template('view.phtml', $args);
```

Arguments are assigned to `$_ARGS` within the template.
In `view.phtml`, you can get the arguments as follows:

```php
<h1>Hello, new world?</h1>
<p>&lt;?php echo $_ARGS['p'] ?&gt;</p>
```

Reload the page in your browser to see if the changes are reflected.
</section>

